1
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:52,660
Welcome to the scene of the International Yo-yo Contest's finals

2
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:56,800
Here we have two competitors fighting for the championship

3
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,660
they are Taro Yamamoto from Fierce Spiral of Japan!

4
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:06,200
and Jacky from Blazing of China!

5
00:03:12,940 --> 00:03:16,320
Captain,fight!!

6
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:24,000
No time to lose! Let's get it started

7
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,740
Go, Avalanche.

8
00:03:48,777 --> 00:03:50,777
Ok, watch it.

9
00:03:51,646 --> 00:03:53,646
Go, Datura

10
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:15,900
You are the only one who can beat the western speed strategy after that man

11
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,600
and defeated many Asian players indeed these years

12
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,600
but don't take your winning for granted today.

13
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:25,120
Just show me what you got.

14
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:49,760
Jacky use the strongest light of refinement at the very beginning

15
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,780
we can see how resolved he is to win

16
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:56,500
Your attack was like the sharpest spear, but…

17
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,560
I have the strongest shield!

18
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,560
Datura!

19
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,800
what

20
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:26,640
Amazing! Taro Yamamoto dissolves Jacky's attack

21
00:05:27,820 --> 00:05:30,840
Evil! He tackled it

22
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:34,400
Didn't think of that, heh? To tackle your super speed

23
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,080
I've acquired an air-whirl ability beyond imagination

24
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:40,040
It's impossible your current can break my solid defense

25
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,860
no matter how strong it is

26
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:45,420
Taro Yamamoto, you wanna keep defensing and go deuce with me?

27
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:50,080
Aha, the game is just on! Check this out!

28
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:10,740
Taro Yamamoto can attack the rival with sound waves! Unbelievable!

29
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:19,180
Can Jacky take it?

30
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:23,060
I didn't know he has such strong power. If it goes on like this…

31
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:25,060
Now you know my strength.

32
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:28,420
Your so-called speed is no use on me

33
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:35,060
You think my super speed can go just this far?

34
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,040
It's no use, Jacky

35
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:52,060
I've told you you cannot break my solid defence however fast you are

36
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:06,960
Now let me show you what's real super speed!

37
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:19,640
Amazing! The harsh sound wave is weakened!

38
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:22,660
what?

39
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Crap!

40
00:07:44,259 --> 00:07:46,259
The time is now!

41
00:07:46,259 --> 00:07:48,259
Avalanche!

42
00:08:07,392 --> 00:08:09,392
Yes!!
He wins!

43
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:19,640
The champion of this international yo-yo individual final is…Jacky from China!!

44
00:08:45,131 --> 00:08:47,131
Hey, done!

45
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:52,460
Oh, break the record again, boring!

46
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:56,120
Is there no game that can challenge me now?

47
00:08:56,418 --> 00:08:58,418
What's up there?

48
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:06,760
Excuse me, excuse me…hey, What's this?

49
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:13,880
This is the latest electronic game of yo-yo

50
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:18,360
It's exciting, and there is a secret present for getting a full score.

51
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:23,040
But no one can ever make it, pity

52
00:09:23,055 --> 00:09:25,055
No one?

53
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,080
Hey! What are you doing?!

54
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,400
There is a double battle in this game, isn't it?

55
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:37,900
I just wanna try it out with you. Come on!

56
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:42,080
Ok,let's do it

57
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,820
This is the secret present for winners?

58
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:13,740
Impossible! This game has been out for less than two days

59
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:15,740
how did you make it?

60
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:20,200
Hey, kid, you know who I am?

61
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,100
I am the legendary game killer Liam!!

62
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:26,980
I created all high score record in all games here

63
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:33,200
You don't have to feel sad for losing to such a master-hand like me,hahaha...

64
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:36,520
What's the big deal wining a electronic game

65
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:41,200
You are nothing unless you can play the real yo-yo!

66
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,860
what!

67
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:47,120
Tell me after you've seen a real yo-yo!

68
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:55,420
You bully, what's so proudful defeating a Fire Soldier

69
00:10:57,297 --> 00:10:59,297
Real yo-yo?

70
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:11,480
Just a string and a ball

71
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:14,600
What's the fun? Right

72
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:26,100
Watch my spring shooting stunt!

73
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:33,280
Fail. try again

74
00:11:35,692 --> 00:11:37,692
It is a little hard

75
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:40,720
but I don't believe I can't make it. Hey!

76
00:11:44,777 --> 00:11:46,777
Ouch!

77
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,980
That was awesome

78
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:59,980
How could you make the move?

79
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:01,980
It's easy. Let me show you

80
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:07,440
No problem. Watch this

81
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:10,600
Your yo-yo really can be assembled freely?

82
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,800
Of course!

83
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,220
I call it "Bipolar"

84
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:15,600
It can transform into different shapes

85
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:20,440
and change the configuration according to different needs during matches

86
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:23,580
In that case, the rival will be confused

87
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:25,380
That's crafty

88
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,380
What are you guys doing here?

89
00:12:27,660 --> 00:12:29,660
Captain.

90
00:12:32,537 --> 00:12:33,697
Captain.

91
00:12:33,697 --> 00:12:35,697
Tomorrow is the team finals

92
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:39,020
Why you guys are not practicing but idling out here?

93
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:41,020
He is the champion in the individual finals.

94
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:43,020
His name is …Jacky

95
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,700
Congrats for the championship

96
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,440
You are Jacky, right? Can you show us a move?

97
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:53,100
Sorry, I don't have the time now. let's go

98
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:07,640
Captain, we met some other players when practicing

99
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:10,860
so … we were just having a trial with them

100
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:14,560
Yes, and we were going back…

101
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:20,760
Do you ever understand the importance of tomorrow's competition to us?

102
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,420
Haven't I told you we should meet it ahead-on at our best?

103
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:26,420
Yeah, we…

104
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,980
This is a rare chance to come to Japan

105
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:33,560
. I don't see anything wrong with communicating with players from other places

106
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,480
Even you also…

107
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:44,900
Everyone is hungry, let's get something to eat first

108
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,900
That sounds great.

109
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,660
Wow, the noodles here are just delicious!

110
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:57,180
Captain, you've defeated Taro Yamamoto today

111
00:13:57,400 --> 00:14:01,780
There should be no problem in tomorrow's battle with his team, right?

112
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:08,060
I 've told you not to slacken no matter how confident you are.

113
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:12,720
Netherless, this is the best chance to show our team's strength

114
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,760
Yes, I think so too

115
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:19,000
Right. I just heard that the legendary man

116
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,980
will show up in the award presentation. Is that true?

117
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:22,980
Is it?

118
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:28,800
That is what you are nervous for, no wonder…

119
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:32,240
That guy is the goal of every Chinese yo-yo player

120
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:35,900
It is just gorgeous to receive the prize from him!!

121
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,540
No

122
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,020
what!

123
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:45,080
He is not just my goal. I wanna surpass him!

124
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:50,400
My dream will come true as that we win tomorrow's team championship

125
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:03,220
Why is this "Three Leaf Clover" so hard this time.

126
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:04,340
Try again

127
00:15:09,979 --> 00:15:11,979
I made it!

128
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:15,320
That was just a basic move, what's so exciting?

129
00:15:16,831 --> 00:15:18,831
Yeah, me again

130
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:22,860
Oh, it's you,loser

131
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:27,680
Loser? Do you have the gut to try this with me?

132
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:30,120
But how? It's not even a game

133
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:34,420
I make a move, and you follow

134
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:36,960
If you can't, you lose.

135
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:40,100
What? Scared?

136
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,280
Why not? You think I'm scared of you?

137
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:45,220
Ready? Begin!

138
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:59,080
Lightening's performance is just marvelous

139
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:01,520
How many scores will they get?

140
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,840
The final average score is 7.5!

141
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:08,140
Now let's welcome the host team of this international

142
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:11,800
Yo-yo contest's team finals--Fierce Spiral from Japan!

143
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,640
Give them your big hands.

144
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:29,420
It seems the only matched rival to us in these five teams is Fierce Spiral

145
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:34,060
Their captain lost in the individual finals. I don't think they can be any batter

146
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:37,200
Uh uh. This is another story

147
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:39,559
Besides the level of difficulty in techniques

148
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,920
teamwork and coordination between members is just as important

149
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:45,780
Individual's ability can't decide anything

150
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:47,400
don't despise the team

151
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,400
Yes, captain

152
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,300
Now，it's the Fierce Spiral's show time!

153
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:29,940
They are even better than I expected

154
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:34,360
Both their creativeness and coordination are just perfect

155
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:37,360
Captain, what shall we do now?

156
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:39,900
Jacky.

157
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:53,980
The Fierce spiral's performance was just flawless

158
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,680
Oh, here we have have the results

159
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:59,200
Their final average score is 9.5!

160
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:05,560
This is the highest mark ever scored in this contest

161
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:09,220
Show them your congratulations with big hands!

162
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:14,240
Get a 9.5 in an international contest? They are really good

163
00:18:15,838 --> 00:18:17,838
It's no big deal

164
00:18:18,780 --> 00:18:22,760
Dazzle Fire led by that guy made a world record of 9.8!

165
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:25,800
He could do it, I can do it!

166
00:18:27,338 --> 00:18:28,918
Captain.

167
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:33,860
Listen, though Fierce Spiral has better coordination than we thought

168
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:38,160
and they must have a very high score at creativeness for their novel performing style

169
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:40,180
we can defeat them and turn the tables

170
00:18:40,180 --> 00:18:44,080
as long as we make greater effort at upgrading techniques difficulty

171
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:47,660
But our moves were already set. We...

172
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:52,040
Don't worry, just listen to my command later when we get on that stage

173
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:55,780
We win this, I will surpass that guy

174
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:03,860
The next team is Blazing from China!

175
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:07,580
Their captain Jacky has won the single championship

176
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:12,640
Can he lead his team to take home the championship of the team finals?

177
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:14,700
Let's wait and see

178
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,380
Let's begin

179
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:42,720
Why? Why the audience have no respond on our performance?

180
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:47,280
Cause' they have higher expectations after Fierce Spiral's performance

181
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,620
If we don't upgrade the difficulty level, I'm afraid…

182
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:54,040
But it's impossible to change the set of moves we've been practiced for so long

183
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:58,040
Nothing is impossible. I want you to double your speed

184
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:01,340
This is the only way to upgrade the difficulty level

185
00:20:01,340 --> 00:20:03,720
and our last chance to win

186
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:25,460
Blazing Team is amazing! That's so fast! Bravo!

187
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:30,140
China's Blazing really lives up to its reputation

188
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:36,100
The whole team is doing their moves at an increasing speed under Jacky's lead

189
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:42,000
They manage to upgrade the difficulty level by speeding up

190
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,020
but Ken and Jerry...

191
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:54,540
Oh, no! we cannot sustain this speed for long

192
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:58,460
Even if I can , my yo-yo…ah!

193
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,480
"Lonewolf"...no!

194
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:05,540
Change the move to "Around the world", keep two yo-yos as close as possible

195
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:10,460
What?! Use a basic move at such a moment?

196
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:13,280
In that case, two yo-yos will slow down

197
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,280
Trust me!

198
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,960
Right now!